Presidents, famous actors, television executives, neighbors and tourists all

had their memories.
Through them all ran a single, constant thread.
They all said they loved Lucy, and they'll miss her.
So did the world," President Bush said in a statement.
She's not gone.
Comedian George Burns, another friend of many years, said, "As long as the world goes on, Lucy will be seen."
"When Gracie died, it was a shock to me," he said.
"This is a shock.
She's a legend.
It's like losing a friend, a family member, instead of a celebrity."
